        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "Technically, it _used_ to work when the shell auto-expanded a bracketed list (`{foo,bar,baz} == \"foo bar baz\"`) due to what I assume was a bug with the Yargs parser. The `--hoist` option has _always_ been severely overloaded, and it was only a matter of time before our dirty hacks ran afoul of parser correctness.\r\n\r\nI would appreciate a PR that documents this wrinkle (proposing the alternatives you've moved towards). I don't think we should spend any time hacking Yargs to \"understand\" our mutant usage.",
